19. Praxeas. Praxeas, an Asiatio by birth, was a Monarchian who spent a short time in Rome during the episcopate of Zephyrinus, whose Montanism he successfully combated, and then passed to Karthago. Our knowledge oi him is derived from Tertullian's trectise ‘Adversus Praxean’ which is a general refutation of patripassian opinions. Praxeas is not mentioned by Hippolytus, nor by any earlier writer than Augustius except Tertullian and the present author.
